cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use NODIS in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "NODIS: NOdewise De-sparsified Inference Statistics"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/youwillfindinfinity/nodis"
authors:
  - family-names: Bumbuc
    given-names: Roland
    affiliation: "Amsterdam UMC, University of Amsterdam"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX"
abstract: >
  NODIS is a Python-native package for edge-level statistical inference in
  Gaussian Graphical Models, providing de-sparsified nodewise Lasso p-values,
  confidence intervals, and FDR-controlled adjacency matrices for
  high-dimensional gene co-expression network analysis.
keywords:
  - gaussian graphical models
  - gene co-expression networks
  - statistical inference
  - de-sparsified lasso
  - bioinformatics
  - high-dimensional statistics
preferred-citation:
